003C/div>",{"id":243,"html":244},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001314_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001314_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001314.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001314-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":246,"html":247},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text from photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":249,"html":250},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>To the gods of the underworld. Myrtale, most worthy, lived for 30 years, 3 months. Kornelios Agathemeros made this for his most devoted partner in life.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":249,"html":252},"\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">Serena Agodi\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Agli dèi del mondo sotterraneo. Myrtale, degnissima, visse 30 anni e 3 mesi. Kornelios Agathemeros lo ha fatto per la sua devotissima compagna di vita.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":254,"html":255},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp> This epitaph was found together with IG 14.485 (exhibition no.26), which was apparently erected in memory of the same man as set up this text (although it is also possible that they are father and son). The implication is that Myrtale was his first wife and that he remarried (to Euphrosyne) after her death. The differing letter forms and use of Greek numerals indicate that this was engraved by a different stonemason.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":257,"html":258},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Franz 1853 5717 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">492\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Korhonen 2004 111 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":260,"html":261},"handnote"," \u003Cp> Line 1  16-22  Interlineation line 1 to 2  not measured  \u003C/p>",{"id":263,"html":264},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  ",[266,268,271,272],{"html":267},"Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: #JP",{"id":269,"lang":137,"html":270},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">Θ\u003C/span>(εοῖς) \u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">Κ\u003C/span>(αταχθονίοις) \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Μυρτάλη\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Μυρτάλη\">Μυρτάλη\u003C/span>\u003C/span> χρηστο-\u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>τάτη ἔζησεν ἔτη \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">λ\u003C/span>´ μῆν(ας) \u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">γ\u003C/span>´ \u003Cspan data-type=\"pers